<HEADLINE> U.S. President to Visit Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien Wednesday announced a working visit by U.S. President
Bill Clinton on October 8, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister said in his announcement that the two
countries would review "a wide range of bilateral and multilateral
issues of interest" during the visit.
</P>
<P>
Clinton is also invited to address the International Conference
on Federalism to be held in Mont-Tremblant, Quebec, the Canadian
Prime Minister said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
