<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nuclear Techniques Widely Used in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The peaceful use of nuclear
techniques in Zambia has spread over several sectors in Zambia,
namely health, industry, education, agriculture and mining, a
Zambian official said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Gavin Silwamba, acting director general of Central Board of
Health, told the opening of a three-day seminar on security and
safety of nuclear materials and radioactive sources that "with
this in mind, the benefits that will arise from the knowledge
gained from this workshop will be invariably spread over these
different sectors."
</P>
<P>
However, he said, five cases of attempted illicit trafficking
of spent nuclear materials have almost taken place in the country
in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Fortunately these sources did not end up in health hazard or
deaths due to timely action by the security agencies and the
regulatory authorities, he told the regional seminar.
</P>
<P>
Silwamba challenged the participants to ensure that a safe
environment prevails for their respective communities.
</P>
<P>
This seminar will provide good opportunities for those who are
involved in obtaining relevant information to detect and control
the irregular and in most cases, clandestine movement of nuclear
and radioactive materials, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
