<HEADLINE> Cape Verde Appoints New Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LUANDA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Rui Figueiredo Soares will take
the position of foreign minister of Cape Verde, replacing the
out-going Jose Luis de Jesus, Prime Minister Carlos Veiga
announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to Veiga, the inaugural ceremony for Soares, former
Minister of Presidency of the Council of Ministers, will be held
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Veiga said he would nominate a new minister to replace Soares
former post, but didn't give any details.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister also designated Olavo Correia as the new
governor of the national bank Banco de Cabo Verde.
</P>
<P>
Jesus offered his resignation on May 25 when he had decided to
 campaign for the grand judge of the International Tribunal of
Maritime Laws, which has its headquarters in Germany.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that Jesus will soon take up his office as a
judge of the International Tribunal of Maritime Laws. 
</P>
</TEXT>
