<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Condemns Israel's Blocking of Al-Aqsa Mosque </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Wednesday condemned the
blocking of the entrance gate to famous Al-Aqsa Mosque in
Jerusalem, calling on "followers of Islam and all divine religions
to show suitable reaction to it."
</P>
<P>
According to the official Islamic Republic News Agency, Foreign
Ministry spokesman Hamid-Reza Asefi said Israel's "continued
desecration of Muslim sanctities indicated that the entity is
negligent of the sanctities of all divine religions, especially
those of the world of Islam.
</P>
<P>
He said the international community shoulders a grave
responsibility towards the issue and urged the Muslim world to
"concentrate efforts on liberating" Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
"The international community is expected to use all its means
to prevent gradual demographic changes in the holy Gods (Jerusalem)
and adopt serious measures against the Zionist regime," Asefi
said.
</P>
<P>
Israeli police Tuesday sealed an opening in the outer
wall of the Al Aqsa Mosque compound, Islam's third holiest site.
</P>
<P>
The action was approved by Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak in
coordination with the public security ministry.
</P>
<P>
The closure came when the wall opening of the mosque was under
renovation by the Islamic Trust. During the recent renovations, a
window on the compound's outer wall, which is not far from the
Western Wall, Judaism's most sacred site, was enlarged into a
door-sized opening.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Internal Security Minister Shlomo Ben-Ami said that
the enlargement of the window was a violation of the unwritten
agreement between the Israeli authority and the Islamic Trust that
neither side introduce changes at the holy site. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
