<HEADLINE> France Deplores Attacks by Armed Groups in Russian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 11 (Xinhua) -- France expressed on Wednesday its
regret about the latest attacks by armed groups in Russia's
Caucasus region, and recalled its support to Russia in maintaining
the latter's territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
``France is worried by the events affecting some villages in
south Daguestan,'' said French Foreign Ministry assistant
spokesman Francois Rivasseau.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the latest attacks took place in one of
Russia's poorest regions which has suffered from a recent war in
Chechnya.
</P>
<P>
Several dozen people were killed in the fightings which took
place between Russian troops and security forces, and some armed
groups infiltrating into Russia's Daguestan Republic from Chechnya
since last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The armed groups claimed themselves to be ``wahhabists,'' or
radical Islamists. 
</P>
