<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former Rwandan Minister Held Responsible for Rape </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The indictment of the
former Rwandan Minister for Family and Women's Affairs, Pauline
Nyiramasuhuko, has been amended to include six additional counts,
one of which accuses her of being responsible for rape.
</P>
<P>
Nyiramasuhuko is held responsible for rape "as part of a
widespread and systematic attack against a civilian population on
political, ethnic and racial grounds" in Butare, central Rwanda,
the International Criminal Tribunal for Rwanda (ICTR) said in a
press release available here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The accused is jointly charged with her son, Arsene Shalom
Ntahobali, a former businessman and leader of a local militia,
said the U.N. court based in Tanzania's northern town of Arusha.
</P>
<P>
In the previous indictment, only Ntahobali who now faces four
new counts, was charged with committing crimes of sexual violence.
 The two are now jointly charged with ten counts of genocide,
conspiracy to commit genocide, and crimes against humanity.
</P>
<P>
Nyiramasuhuko faces a separate charge of direct and public
incitement to commit genocide.
</P>
<P>
The accused, with the absence of soldiers and others, were
alleged to have set up road blocks, where they identified,
abducted and killed members of the Tutsi population. When
abducting their victims, they often forced them to undress
completely before forcing them into vehicles and taking them to
deaths.
</P>
<P>
The indictment further alleges that Ntahobali, assisted by
unknown " accomplices," participated in the kidnapping and raping
of Tutsi women.
</P>
<P>
At least 500,000 people, mostly Tutsis, were allegedly killed
in 1994 Rwanda genocide. The U. N. Security Council set up the
court in Arusha to try the chief suspects of the genocide.
</P>
<P>
The former minister was arrested on July 18 in Nairobi, Kenya
and transferred on the same day to Arusha.
</P>
<P>
Her son was arrested on July 24 and transferred on the same day
to the town. 
</P>
</TEXT>
