<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rwanda Hosts Sub-regional Workshop on Human Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 11 (Xinhua) -- A sub-regional workshop on human
rights, jointly sponsored by the Rwandan National University and
the International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC), opened in
Rwanda's second-largest city Butare Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The focus of the two-day seminar will be the humanitarian law
and human rights in armed conflicts, the Rwanda News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
According to Mario Musa, head of ICRC communications
department, the workshop has been organized in preparation for the
50th anniversary of the Geneva Convention which falls on August
12.
</P>
<P>
Topics to be discussed at the workshop include the origin and
evolution of humanitarian rights, the origin and role of Rwandan
Red Cross, humanitarian international law, Rwandan internal law,
and the repression of crimes committed during armed conflicts.
</P>
<P>
The participants will also assess the status of refugees in
case of war and prisoners of war in the international law, women
and children victims of humanitarian violations and responsibility
of military officers in armed conflicts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
