<HEADLINE> France Calls on India, Pakistan to Exercise Restraint </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 11 (Xinhua) -- France Wednesday called on India
and Pakistan to exercise the greatest restraint, after India shot
down a Pakistani military aircraft on Tuesday and Pakistan tried
to shoot down an Indian helicopter on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
``We call on the two countries to show their greatest restraint
and resume bilateral dialogue in the spirit of the meeting of
Lahore last February,'' said French Foreign Ministry assistant
spokesman Francois Rivasseau.
</P>
<P>
Indian Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee visited Pakistan on
February 20 and 21, during which he held talks with his Pakistani
counterpart Nawaz Sharif on major issues of dispute, including the
problem of Jammu and Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
But the two countries went to a limited war in May over Kashmir
and relations between them remained tense since then. 
</P>
