<HEADLINE> Albanian Government Sticks to "One China" Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Albanian Government Sticks to
"one China" policy, Albanian Foreign Ministry Spokesman Sokol
Gjoka reiterated here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Gjoka made this remark during an interview by Xinhua reporters
here on the Albania-China relations.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government upheld "one China" policy in the past,
it still upholds this policy now, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Recently, some local media reported that a few people in
Albania are pushing Albania to run after Macedonia to establish
relations with Taiwan as a bid to trade Taiwan's economic aid for
Albania. Commenting on that, Gjoka said that it was not the voice
of the Albanian Government.
</P>
<P>
The reports carried on one or two Albanian television stations
and one local newspaper just reflected the points of view of some
individuals.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the current relations between Albania and China,
Gjoka said: "bilateral relations between the two countries are
into a high position."
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government and the Chinese government have decided
to take concrete steps to strengthen their relations, he said. The
Albanian-Chinese Joint Economic and Trade Commission is going to
restart its work very soon.
</P>
<P>
There are also other signs which have shown or will demonstrate
that the Albania-China relations will move towards to a
strengthening and very qualitative improvement, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
