<HEADLINE> 21 Smugglers Killed, Drugs Seized in Eastern Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Iran's law enforcement forces
in the eastern province of Khorasan have killed 21 bandits of an
international smuggling gang in an 20-hour operation.
</P>
<P>
Colonel Bahram Nurouzi of provincial police said Wednesday that
another four smugglers managed to escape, according to a report by
the Islamic Republic News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The report failed to mention when the exchange of fire
occurred, but said 16 rocket launchers and 89 kilograms of opium
were seized from the smugglers.
</P>
<P>
This gang had previous records of drug smuggling, the colonel
said, adding the operation was conducted in the vicinity of cities
of Tourbat-Heydarieh and Khwaf in the eastern part of the province.
</P>
<P>
He said the operation was carried out in an unprecedented
magnitude in the province against the smugglers.
</P>
<P>
Iran is used by drug traffickers as a transit to ship narcotics
to European and world markets from the "Gold Crescent" overlapping
parts of Iran, Afghanistan and Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The government has beefed up efforts to crack down on drug
smuggling and imposed harsh punishments on traffickers and
drug-dealers. 
</P>
