<HEADLINE> Prolonged Drought Threatens Life in W. Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Western Uganda is experiencing a
 prolonged dry spell which has constituted a serious threat to the
life of local residents.
</P>
<P>
The drought has caused the death of large stretches of crops
and various domestic animals, Radio Uganda reported Wednesday
evening.
</P>
<P>
"If the government does not take any action against it, people
living there will definitely die," one member of Parliament from
the western region was quoted as saying in the House.
</P>
<P>
The adverse weather has also caused reduction of coffee
production, one of the pillars of the country's foreign exchange
income.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the drying grass, many cows cannot produce milk
as before. Western Uganda is regarded as the main milk provider
for others parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Several MPs requested the government to take immediate and
effective measures to ensure the safety of food and drinking water
for the local residents and domestic animals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
