<HEADLINE> Create Scientific Social Environment to Fight Falun Gong: Commentary (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Much work needs to be done to create a properly civilized and
scientific social environment, and priority should be given to
ideological work, the commentary notes.
</P>
<P>
The article stresses the importance of occupying such
ideological fields as culture, education, and the press and
publications. Otherwise, they will be taken over by anti-Marxism,
non-Marxism and superstition, it says.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should also be made to educate officials and the public
in Marxist materialism, atheism, scientific knowledge, patriotism,
collectivism and socialism, the commentary says.
</P>
<P>
The commentary calls for helping the people to distinguish true
science from pseudo-science, traditional culture from feudalistic
dregs, and normal religious activities from fallacies preached
under the cover of religion.
</P>
<P>
While furthering the crackdown on Falun Gong's illegal
publications, greater efforts should be made to invigorate the
cause of socialist culture and enrich the people's cultural life,
it notes.
</P>
<P>
The creation of a civilized and scientific social environment
is an arduous task, it says, adding that the work should be set
high on the agenda of constructing socialist ethics.
</P>
<P>
The fight against Falun Gong indicates that as long as the
people are mobilized, all evil ideologies will lose ground under
the strong attack of public opinion, the commentary says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
