Museum at the national shrine in order to provide comprehensive
information of Zimbabwe's struggle for independence for the
benefit of future generations.
</P>
<P>
The Zimbabwean president revealed this at an event at the
National Heroes Acre in Harare to pay respects to the fallen
heroes of the liberation struggle that brought about the country's
independence in 1980.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of Zimbabwean people thronged around the acre to mark
the fallen heroes on the Heroes Day.
</P>
<P>
