would soon undertake a feasibility study tour of museums in Egypt
and other countries.
</P>
<P>
The president also said the program of identifying and
rehabilitating the national liberation war graves that were
scattered in neighboring countries was being given top priority by
the government.
</P>
<P>
He said the government would continue to assist widows of the
fallen heroes and their children under the age of 18 years.
</P>
<P>
However, the president stressed the social and economic
interests of Zimbabweans were equally important hence they should
receive the attention of the government.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe also paid tribute to Zimbabwean soldiers fighting in the
 Democratic Republic of the Congo.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwean forces together with those from Angola and Namibia
have been in the Congo since August last year, assisting Congolese
President Laurent Kabila's government to quell rebels backed by
Uganda and Rwanda. 
