<HEADLINE> Yunnan, Taiwan Enhance Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Taiwan's investment in southwest
China's Yunnan Province has exceeded 170 million U.S. dollars,
making Taiwan the third-biggest investor in the province after
Hong Kong and the United States.
</P>
<P>
At a seminar on economic and trade cooperation between Yunnan
and Taiwan, which opened here today, a Yunnan official said that
Taiwan's investment involves 320 projects, ranging from
restaurants and timber processing to real estate.
</P>
<P>
He said that Yunnan's trade volume with Taiwan reached 23.7
million U.S. dollars-worth last year, forming a sharp contrast
with the 1.47 million U.S. dollars-worth in 1987.
</P>
<P>
The number of tourists from Taiwan is also rising constantly,
with nearly one million visitors from the island province coming
to Yunnan over the past ten years, and the figure is expected to
hit 200,000 this year alone. 
</P>
