meeting Wednesday which was chaired by Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif
and was attended by the three chiefs of army staff as well as
senior cabinet ministers.
</P>
<P>
The meeting expressed strong condemnation and indignation over
India's act by violating Pakistan's airspace and shooting down the
unarmed aircraft which was on a routine training mission.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan was fully justified in making an appropriate response
in self-defense to India's "hostile act", said Mushahid.
</P>
<P>
He said the Defense Committee of the Cabinet had ordered
Pakistan's armed forces to "take all necessary measures".
</P>
<P>
Mushahid urged the international community to take "upfront and
principled stand" towards the hostile act by India which, he said,
was not like "a mature, responsible and civilized state". 
