<HEADLINE> Over 100 Kosovo Albanians Rounded up in England </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 11 (Xinhua) -- British police said they had
detained more than 100 people claiming to be ethnic Albanians from
Kosovo in southeast England on early Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It was not immediately known how the 107 apparent refugees had
arrived at Rainham in Kent, where they were rounded up by police
after a local resident called to say he had seen illegal
immigrants near his home.
</P>
<P>
