<HEADLINE> Educational Circles Lash Out at Falun Gong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- China's educational circles
vowed to further expose the true nature of the Falun Gong cult and
strengthen education on materialism and atheism.
</P>
<P>
Education Minister Chen Zhili told a meeting here today that
students and teachers should realize that the struggle against
Falun Gong is a serious political struggle.
</P>
<P>
Falun Gong is a typical illegal organization and a political
force trying to grab the commanding heights from the Communist
Party of China and the government, she said.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi and his organization eroded some people's political
beliefs and ethics, and even won over some weak-minded Party
members and officials, by spreading superstition and theism, the
minister said.
</P>
<P>
The misdeeds of Falun Gong pose great threats to the country's
hard-won political situation of reform, development and stability,
as well as to state power, she said.
</P>
<P>
She called on educational circles across China to further
improve ideological and political education, with universities and
colleges in particular playing a major part in this campaign by
making the most of their intellectual advantages.
</P>
<P>
The participants in the meeting held unanimously that amid the
early success of the struggle everybody should remain sober-minded
about the cult's true nature of being anti-scientific, anti-human
and anti-government, with a hidden political background both at
home and overseas. 
</P>
