<HEADLINE> Chinese Women Win Titles in Rifle 3 Positions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, Croatia, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese women shooters
took the individual and team titles in sports rifle three
positions at the Military World Games here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Shan Hong, World Cup champion in Milan, Italy this year, scored
585 points for the gold, one point better than second placer
Loubov Galkina of Russia.
</P>
<P>
"Today's result was normal because of the wind condition here,"
said Shan, also champion at last December's Asian Games.
</P>
<P>
"I did not perform well in the beginning of the standing
position part," added Shan, whose best result this year was 592
points. "But I adjusted quickly and did well in kneel position."
</P>
<P>
Another Chinese Xu Yimin took home the bronze with 578 points.
Russia's Irina Guerassimenok also had the same total but was
placed fourth because a lower score in the last ten shots. The
third Chinese Wang Xian scored 572 points to place 12th.
</P>
<P>
The same rule gave the Chinese trio, which won the World
Championship last year, the team gold as China and Russia had an
equal total of 1,735. The Russians' total in the last ten shots
was seven points shy of China's.
</P>
<P>
Belarus won the bronze in 1,719 points.
</P>
<P>
The victory avenged China's loss of the team gold medal to
Russia in the women's sports rifle prone by one point on Tuesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
