<HEADLINE> Ship Sails on China's New Shipping Route To Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A container liner sailed from
this south China Special Economic Zone today, marking the opening
of China's new container shipping route to Europe.
</P>
<P>
This is the second shipping route to Europe opened by the
China Shipping Group, a state-run shipping conglomerate based in
Shanghai. Ten container vessels will sail from the Chinese ports
of Dalian, Ningbo, Xiamen, Shenzhen and Hong Kong to Felixstowe,
Rotterdam, Hamburg and Antwerp in Europe, through Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
The first shipping route opened last April. It connects the
Chinese ports of Tianjin, Qingdao, Shanghai and Hong Kong with
Singapore, Rotterdam, Hamburg and Felixstowe, using nine container
ships.
</P>
<P>
The China Shipping Group has assets worth 26.5 billion yuan,
390 vessels with an aggregate capacity of 8.7 million DWT and more
than 40,000 employees.  
</P>
