<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Profile: Mohammad Mohasin, New Chairman of Nepal's National Assembly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 12 (Xinhua) -- National Democratic Party
(RPP) candidate Dr. Mohammad Mohasin was elected chairman of the
National Assembly Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Mohammad Mohasin was born on October 11, 1934. He was awarded
PHD of sociology by Bombay University of India in 1958.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Mohasin became member of the Panchayat (the partyless
system during 1960 and 1990) Philosophy Committee of the Home
Ministry and the Education Plan Drafting Committee of Nepal in
1969. In 1975, he was appointed member-secretary of the
Constitution Reforms and Suggestions Commission.
</P>
<P>
In 1987, Dr. Mohasin became member of National Panchayat, and
was minister of tourism from 1988 to 1990. He was also a member of
the Central Committee of the National Democratic Party-RPP (Chand)
in 1990 and has been a member of the RPP (after unification of
RPP-Chand and RPP-Thapa) central working committee since January
2, 1992.  
</P>
</TEXT>
