<DOCNO> XIE19990812.0083 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Make Its Own Car in December 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The first Bangladesh-made car will
roam in the capital city's streets in December 2000.
</P>
<P>
A Bangladesh National Car Company will be established under a
memorandum of understanding signed here Wednesday between the
NITOL Group of Bangladesh and D&AMP;P Engineering Services of Britain,
the national news agency BSS reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to create 50,000 jobs in making and
selling the car, which, after successful launch, can be exported
to other markets, the BSS said.
</P>
<P>
The cost of each vehicle with a clean efficient petrol engine
will be around 300,000 taka (6,060 U.S. dollars) with
1,100-1,400cc engines.
</P>
<P>
The BSS said the project offers a unique opportunity in the
country's automobile sector.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladesh car program, described as a joint-venture of
strategic alliance, offers total independence and acquisition of
technology because the intellectual rights will become the
property of the Bangladesh National Car Company, unlike the
country's other car projects which rely upon original manufactures
supplying technology.
</P>
<P>
The car, which is to be of versatile design, will meet both the
market and operating conditions in Bangladesh, and all its
variants will be environment-friendly and economical, the news
agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
