<DOCNO> XIE19990812.0091 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Hongzhi's Role in Illegal Gathering at Zhongnanhai (7) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After Li Hongzhi fled out of Beijing, his key followers,
including Li Chang and Wang Zhiwen, were left with the
responsibility of implementing all his plans.
</P>
<P>
At 8:30 am on April 24, a "regular meeting of studying Falun
Dafa" was held by the leaders of the Beijing General Station of
the Society and sub-stations in counties and districts in Beijing
at the address of 7 Cangjingguan Lane, in eastern Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Li and Wang said at the meeting that the date for the illegal
gathering near Zhongnanhai compound would be April 25. The
leaders of substations were assigned the tasks of security,
transportation, order, and sanitary matters at the gathering site.
</P>
<P>
They set the strategy for the illegal gathering as "no slogans,
no banners, no flyers, no fierce verbal attacks, and no revelation
of the organizer -- the Falun Dafa Research Society."
</P>
<P>
Deputy director of the General Station in Beijing Liu Zhichun
was told to inform all the sub-stations in Beijing, and Wang
Zhiwen was responsible for the areas outside Beijing.
</P>
<P>
An announcement created by Li Hongzhi himself was also made
during the meeting to coax practitioners out onto the streets. It
was: everyone should stand up to fulfill their dues for the
protection of Falun Dafa, and their actions should be individually
voluntary.
</P>
<P>
It is evident that Li was taking advantage of his capacity as "
tutor" and "master" to realize his own political ambitions, and at
the same time attempting to prevent his illegal organization from
being exposed.
</P>
<P>
On the afternoon of April 24, the Falun Dafa Research Society
and its Beijing General Station convened another meeting of key
figures to further mobilize practitioners for the next day's move.
</P>
<P>
They set up "command headquarters" and a liaison center,
designated two persons responsible for communications between the
gathering site and the headquarters, and another one responsible
for propaganda to be published on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Li Chang further stressed that leaders above the level of
general stations must refrain from appearing at the gathering site
for fear of being recognized by practitioners.
</P>
<P>
Afterwards, Wang Zhiwen made numerous calls to local Falun Gong
leaders in the provinces of Hebei, Shandong, Liaoning and the
city of Tianjin, asking them to organize followers to go to the
Zhongnanhai compound on the morning of April 25 to "protect Falun
Dafa".
</P>
<P>
Now, "all the preparations for the April 25 action were ready,
" as Li Chang admitted later.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990812.0092 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Hongzhi's Role in Illegal Gathering at Zhongnanhai (8) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- The first group of Falun Gong practitioners arrived at the
northern gate of the Zhongnanhai compound as early as 9:40 pm on
April 24;
</P>
<P>
-- At the small hours of 3:07 am on April 25, passenger buses
from nearby Hebei Province arrived too, and people began to get
off. At 3:30 am, another group of practitioners gathered at the
moat river near Zhongnanhai;
</P>
<P>
-- At 5:13 am, a large group of practitioners emerged at the
gate of Beihai Park and walked westward; and at 5:34 am, many
practitioners started to emerge from lanes;
</P>
<P>
-- And by 7:00 am, a large-scale sit-in had been formed at the
western gate of Zhongnanhai.
</P>
<P>
The size of the sit-in kept growing, and exceeded 10,000 by
later that morning.
</P>
<P>
At 8:00 am, Xinhua reporters arrived at the site and saw that
the streets were full of Falun Gong practitioners, most being the
elderly, women, and peasants from the countryside.
</P>
<P>
When questioned, a peasant woman from Beijing outskirts said
they were practicing Falun Gong . When asked why they were doing
it near Zhongnanhai, she refused to answer.
</P>
<P>
The practitioners kept coming in the afternoon, and pedestrian
traffic on the street in front of the western gate of Zhongnanhai
was totally impossible, and Chang'an Avenue also was seriously
affected.
</P>
<P>
According to previous planned arrangements, Li Chang, Wang
Zhiwen, Ji Liewu and some 20 other key figures gathered at the "
command headquarters" at the home of Yao Jie. At 9:00 am, the sit-
in site reported to the "headquarters" that four representatives
were sent to talk with the central government, but they could not
explain clearly the reason for the gathering.
</P>
<P>
The sit-in site requested capable people from the Falun Dafa
Research Society or its Beijing General Station to come out for
the "dialogue".
</P>
<P>
Finally, Li Chang and Wang Zhiwen decided to come out of the
closet, and headed a five-member "delegation" to enter into the
Zhongnanhai compound for "dialogue".
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990812.0093 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Hongzhi's Role in Illegal Gathering at Zhongnanhai (9) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Li Hongzhi, now in Hong Kong, was by no means inactive. He was
in close touch with the Beijing "headquarters," hearing reports
and issuing orders. Evidence shows that there were over 20 calls
placed between Li and the "headquarters" on April 25, and that
all the actions in Beijing were taken after being directed by Li
Hongzhi.
</P>
<P>
When the sit-in reached the size of 10,000 people, Ji Liewu
informed Li, and Li asked, "Are there many practitioners from
outside Beijing?"  When he was told that the first two groups of
"negotiators" were sent to Zhongnanhai, Li said, "All right."
</P>
<P>
Li also asked Ji, "Why don't you go to Zhongnanhai now that
they (the government) want to talk with you?"
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Municipal Government issued a decree demanding that
the demonstrators leave. Li Hongzhi told Ji that they should still
wait until the "negotiators" came out. The five "negotiators"
headed by Li Chang pestered the Letters and Calls Bureau of the
State Council for nearly nine hours.
</P>
<P>
When the "negotiators" all came out, Li asked how it was going.
Ji answered that the talks would continue the next day. Then, Li
said that the practitioners besieging Zhongnanhai may leave.
</P>
<P>
At around 6:00 am on April 26, when Li came to know that his "
negotiators" were not talking with leaders of the central
government, he called Ji Liewu to furiously blame Li Chang for
calling off the sit-in before talking to top officials.
</P>
<P>
With pieces of evidence coming together, it is now known that
the April 25 illegal gathering at Zhongnanhai was a premeditated
and well-organized political incident aimed at exerting pressure
on the Party and the government and unsettling the country.
</P>
<P>
And evidence shows that Li Hongzhi was the behind-the-scene
chief organizer of the all illegal activities, from the attacks on
the Beijing TV Station to the escalation of the sit-in
demonstration in Tianjin, and to the April 25 illegal gathering in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
However, the man who claims to possess supernatural powers has
overestimated his own power. He is no more than an ant trying
vainly to topple a tree, and he will be tried by history. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
