<HEADLINE> Senior Tibetan Official Meets Ukrainian Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The economy in Tibet is less
developed due to the constant disturbance of the Dalai group as
well as poor natural conditions, a senior Tibetan official said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Basang, deputy secretary of the Chinese Communist Party's
Committee in the Tibet Autonomous Region, told a visiting group
from the Supreme Council of Ukraine, the parliament of that
country, that great changes have taken place in Tibet in the
fields of economy, culture, education and health care since the
democratic reform in the region in 1959.
</P>
<P>
The Ukrainian group, headed by Nina Ivanovna Karpacheva, the
human rights representative of the parliament, was touring Tibet
at the invitation of the Chinese Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Karpacheva told Basang that the group had held "candid talks"
with citizens of this capital city of the region, on various
aspects of their lives.
</P>
<P>
"We are very pleased to see the smiling faces of the Tibetan
people, who are leading happy lives," she added.
</P>
<P>
"Saying is believing," she said. "People who know little about
Tibet talk nonsense about the region. There is little objective
coverage of Tibet."
</P>
<P>
It was learned that during its stay in Tibet, the group will
visit temples and a prison.  
</P>
