<DOCNO> XIE19990812.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Hongzhi Evades Over 10,000 Yuan in Taxes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Li Hongzhi, founder of the
illegal Falun Gong sect, evaded 10,668 yuan in taxes in 1995, when
he purchased a new house, officials from the local public security
and tax collection departments reported today.
</P>
<P>
Li bought a 145-sq-m residence in the Kaiyun residential
district in this capital of northeast China's Jilin province, for
1,700 yuan per sq m, along with a 21.5-sq-m garage in August 1994.
The total purchasing price was 311,000 yuan, a breath-taking sum
at that time.
</P>
<P>
However, when handling the property rights of the house, Li
produced a counterfeit of the title deed, according to which the
purchasing price had been changed to 800 yuan per sq m, and the
total cost was 132,320 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Li then paid 7,992 yuan or six percent of the purchase price in
taxes to the local relevant department.
</P>
<P>
An official with the local public security department said that
Li should have paid 18,660 yuan, according to the real house price.
His behavior violated the Criminal Law and related tax regulations,
and should be punished, he added.
</P>
<P>
Actually, according to him, this was not Li's first involvement
in tax evasion. Li Hongzhi also avoided taxes of 8,655 yuan
during 1992-1994, when he was engaged in Falun Gong activities.
</P>
</TEXT>
