<HEADLINE> Foreign Diplomats Visit Wreckage Site of Downed Pak Plane </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Thursday took a team
of foreign diplomats to the wreckage site of its navy aircraft
shot down by Indian jets, informed sources said.
</P>
<P>
Military officials from embassies in Pakistan of 28 countries
including the United States, Britain, Germany and France, flew in
five helicopters to the site on a marshland close to the Arabic
Sea coastline.
</P>
<P>
The site, guarded by Pakistani troops, is located some 30
kilometers from the coastal village of Musafirkhana of Thatta
district, Sindh province.
</P>
<P>
The foreign diplomats took photographs and gathered technical
data with Global Positioning System instruments at the site where
the debris of the French-made Atlantic aircraft scattered.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani naval officials briefed foreign military attaches
with the help of maps, telling them that the aircraft was flying
inside Pakistani territory when it was attacked Tuesday, said the
sources. 
</P>
