<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Sun Yue Not Play FIVB Macao GP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese top spiker Sun Yue will
not compete in the FIVB World Grand Prix in Macao next week and
can not be back on court within one or two months, China's
national team coach Hu Jin said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"Sun could move forward and backforward, but not to the sides,"
Hu said here. "She needs one or two months to get fully recovery."
</P>
<P>
Team doctor Tian Yongfu said the 26-year-old is recovering soon
from a ligament injury in her left knee sustained in a collision
with a Cuban player in June's Swiss International Women's
Volleyball Championship.
</P>
<P>
"I feel good and want to be back soon," Sun said.
</P>
<P>
Sun said she is looking forward to competing in the Asian
Championships in Hong Kong of China on September 18-26, and the
World Cup in Japan on November 2-16.
</P>
<P>
China will meet Brazil, Italy and the Netherlands in the Macao
Grand Prix slated for August 13-22. 
</P>
</TEXT>
