<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepal Elects National Assembly Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Dr. Mohammad Mohasin of
Rashtriya Prajatantra Party (RPP) was elected Thursday chairman of
the National Assembly, the upper house of Nepali Parliament.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Mohasin secured 30 votes in the 60-member National
Assembly, including 23 from Nepali Congress (NC), three from the
RPP and four from the Communist Party of Nepal (Unified
Marxist-Leninist, UML).
</P>
<P>
Among the five candidates contesting for the post were Basudev
Risal of Nepali Congress, Bachaspati Devkota of the Communist
Party of Nepal (UML), royal nominee Janardan Acharya, and Dr. Ram
Man Shrestha of the Communist Party of Nepal (Marxist-Leninist,
ML).
</P>
<P>
Of the 60 seats in the upper house, the ruling NC has 24,
CPN-UML has 17, 10 are nominated by the king, three each from the
RPP (Thapa) and CPN-ML, two from the RPP (Chand) and one from
Nepal Goodwill Party.
</P>
<P>
The tenure of the chairman of the upper house is six years.
Outgoing chairman Beni Bahadur Karki was elected in 1993 and his
tenure ended on June 26, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The election on July 14 this year failed to produce a upper
house chairman as royal nominee candidate Ramesh Nath Pandey was a
single vote short of a majority. The other two candidates for the
July 14 election were Basudey Risal of (NC) and Dr. Mohammad
Mohasin of the RPP.
</P>
<P>
Of the 60 members of the upper house, 10 are nominated by the
king, 35 including at least three women members are elected by the
House of Representatives and 15 are elected from the five
Development Regions of Nepal with three from each. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
