<HEADLINE> American Seaman Drowns in Singapore River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 12 (Xinhua) -- An American seaman from a
visiting U.S. aircraft carrier drowned in the Singapore River
while on shore leave, Television Corporation of Singapore (TCS)
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
TCS said the body of the drowned has been founded and dragged
to shore but his name has been withheld pending notification to
his next-of-kin.
</P>
<P>
Police said the 21-year-old seaman had apparently fallen into
the river near River Walks Apartments at about 1:30 a.m. after a
night out with a group of other seamen in the Boat Quay area,
where various bars and restaurants stand in great numbers.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Embassy in Singapore has confirmed the deceased was a
member of the USS Constellation aircraft carrier which is in
Singapore on a five-day visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
