<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "China Playing More Important Role in UPU" (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- "The upcoming 22nd Congress of
the Universal Postal Union (UPU), to be held in this Chinese
capital, will enable the country to work more closely with the UPU,
" said Liu Huasheng, deputy director of the secretariat of the
Congress's organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
Liu was the first Chinese to serve in the UPU headquarters in
Bern, Switzerland, where he worked for six years from 1980, and
has been in charge of contacts between China and the UPU ever
since.
</P>
<P>
Eighty-five years ago, when China joined the UPU officially,
the delegates representing China to UPU meetings were from the
United Kingdom. It was not until 1972 that the legal status of the
People's Republic of China (PRC) in the UPU was resumed, and that
was 23 years after the founding of the PRC.
</P>
<P>
"The image of the Chinese delegation to the UPU is improving
all the time, since its debut in 1972, and China's role in the
organization is becoming more and more important," Liu said.
</P>
<P>
In the 1970s, hardly any voice from China could be heard at UPU
congresses, for the Chinese delegates lacked knowledge of the
regulations and topics under discussion. Some of them even
regarded such topics as competition in the postal market as
irrelevant to China, the economy of which was a planned one at the
time.
</P>
<P>
However, China became prominent as a spokesman for the
interests of developing countries during that period. During the
17th UPU Congress in Lausanne, Switzerland, China and other
countries successfully helped the Democratic People's Republic of
Korea to join the UPU in the face of opposition from some Western
countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990812.0122 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "China Playing More Important Role in UPU" (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the 1980s, China began to take an active part in all the
activities of the UPU, and played important roles in many key
departments, according to Liu.
</P>
<P>
For instance, China was appointed to take charge of a special
panel to coordinate the solution of terminal fees, the most
contentious issue of the postal service at the time, at the Seoul
Congress.
</P>
<P>
In 1987 the UPU expressed its wish to see China hosting the
Postal Congress, for it believed in China's capability to hold
such an international event, Liu said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government attached great importance to the
application for hosting the event. President Jiang Zemin assumed
the office of honorary chairman of the organizing committee of the
congress, with vice-premier Wu Bangguo taking the position of
chairman.
</P>
<P>
"Held at the turn of the century in Beijing, the upcoming
Congress will promote the relations between China and the UPU in
the next millennium," Liu commented.
</P>
<P>
The 22nd UPU Congress, the first UPU meeting ever held in China,
is slated for August 23 to September 15. More than 2,000 delegates
from the 189 member nations of the UPU and over 20 international
organizations will attend the conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
