<DOCNO> XIE19990812.0123 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Stresses Importance of Reform of SOEs (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
called on localities to seize the opportunity to push ahead with
the reform and development of State-owned enterprises (SOEs) and
make breakthroughs in this regard.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also general secretary of the Chinese Communist
Party Central Committee, made this call in a speech delivered at
an August 11-12 meeting at which he presided in this city in
northeast China's Liaoning Province on the reform and development
of SOEs in north China's eight provinces and municipalities.
</P>
<P>
"The period from now to the end of the first decade of the next
century is a crucial stage in China's reform and development.
During this time we should do our utmost to form a relatively
sound socialist market economic system, and sustain rapid and
healthy economic growth," Jiang emphasized.
</P>
<P>
This is necessary for the country to realize its trans-century
objectives in the modernization drive, and also for maintaining
and developing the hard-won situation of reform, development and
stability, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"The good performance of SOEs not only is a major economic
issue that concerns healthy and long-term economic development,
but also a major political issue that concerns the fate of the
socialist system," he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The reform and development of SOEs is an important task for the
whole of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and also a glorious
mission history has offered to this generation of the Chinese
people, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"Under the guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory, the Party's basic
line and the rich experience drawn from the last two decades of
reform, we have every reason to blaze a new trail in this regard,
as we now have greater national strength and a more solid material
and technological foundation, as well as the enthusiastic
involvement of the people as a whole," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The Party secretaries of Beijing and Tianjin municipalities,
and Hebei, Shanxi, Jilin, Liaoning and Heilongjiang provinces, and
the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, attended the meeting and
gave briefings on the operations of SOEs in their areas. Managers
of some large SOEs in these areas gave some additional
explanations. All the participants were optimistic about the
reform of SOEs, promising to lead vigorous and prosperous SOEs
into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang spoke highly of the great contributions made by the
people of north China to the national economy and the achievements
in the reform and development of SOEs.
</P>
<P>
This is the fifth time this year that Jiang has presided over
meetings on this subject. In today's speech, he focused on
unswervingly promoting the reform and development of SOEs, further
speeding up its pace and strengthening the Party's leadership in
this regard.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
