<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taliban Say Will Not Extradite Osama to U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban militia
Thursday denied reports that Saudi dissident Osama bin Laden has
training camps in Afghanistan and reiterated that they will not
hand him over to the United States, news reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban statement came at a time when the United States was
reportedly preparing for a raid on Afghanistan to capture the
alleged terrorist who tops the Federal Bureau of Investigation's
10 most wanted men.
</P>
<P>
"Osama is in Afghanistan... but has no military training camps
in Afghanistan," said Maulwi Wakil Ahmed Mutawakil, spokesman for
the Islamic militia.
</P>
<P>
He said that "all of the activities of Osama have been stopped"
in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Mutawakil reiterated that the Taliban will not hand over Osama
to the United States because "America cannot provide any evidence
or any proof" that he is involved in terrorist activities.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
