<DOCNO> XIE19990812.0125 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan-China Trade Rises in First Half of 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Bilateral trade between Japan and
China rose 8.5 percent in the first six months of 1999 to 29.8
billion U.S. dollars, a Japanese semi-governmental trade
organization said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The figure is second only to a record January-June high of 29.
93 billion dollars set in 1997, the Japan External Trade
Organization (JETRO) said.
</P>
<P>
Japan's exports to China grew 11.1 percent to 10.68 billion
dollars, with those of chemical products and electronic parts
increasing 23 percent and 21 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Imports from China increased 7.2 percent to 19.12 billion
dollars, including a 9 percent growth in imports of textile
products and a 22 percent surge in imports of fishery products.
</P>
<P>
JETRO also predicted comparable growth in Sino-Japanese trade
for the second half of 1999, expanding bilateral trade for the
whole year by about 10 percent over the 56.9 billion dollars
registered in the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
