<DOCNO> XIE19990812.0126 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Stresses Importance of Reform of SOEs (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang praised the SOEs and the working class for their great
contributions to the country over the past 50 years, adding that
SOEs have been growing steadily since the reform and opening
policies were introduced at the end of 1978.
</P>
<P>
However, many problems such as falling economic returns, heavy
debts and surplus workers still plague SOEs, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang urged government departments at all levels to pay greater
attention to the problems, and take concrete measures to solve
them, as the reform of SOEs has entered a crucial stage.
</P>
<P>
He also called for more care for the laid-off workers, saying
that improving their lives and ensuring their reemployment is a
major political responsibility of the government.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the importance of properly handling the relations
between reform, development and stability, saying that social
stability must be taken into account while promoting reform to
ensure the long-term stability of the country.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that, in the course of developing the socialist
productive forces and promoting the industrialization and
modernization of the country, SOEs, especially large and medium-
sized enterprises, must play a pillar role.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, measures must be taken to explore ways to establish
a modern enterprise system conforming to the market economy, and
improve their management and competitiveness to ensure their
healthy development.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also stressed the importance of maintaining and
increasing the value of State-owned assets, saying that they are
the common property of the people as a whole. Therefore, effective
supervision must be carried out to guarantee that State-owned
assets and their rights and interests are not violated.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990812.0127 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Stresses Importance of Reform of SOEs (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In order to shake off burdens and seek new development
opportunities, SOEs should step up technological upgrading and
industry rebuilding, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that SOEs should bear in mind the fact that science
and technology are the primary production force, and pay more
attention to production quality and efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Jiang pointed out that SOEs should also have a
disciplined, capable and experienced leadership. He said that
personnel reforms should be further promoted and a market mechnism
should be introduced to choose SOE leaders.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Jiang also put special emphasis on the
development of leadership in the SOEs. He said that adherence to
Communist Party leadership is a basic political principle, and the
guarantee for the smooth progress of all socialist causes.
</P>
<P>
"The more complicated the global environment is, the more
weighty and arduous our reform and development will be, and the
more important the task of strengthening party leadership," Jiang
noted.
</P>
<P>
He urged SOE leaders to stand in the forefront of the reform
and make sure that key government policies and decisions are
carried out.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that the overall development situation of the
SOEs is good, indicating that the government's policies concerning
the SOEs and on stimulating domestic demand are correct.
</P>
<P>
He said that the goal of the reforms and development of the
SOEs will be accomplished, so long as all SOEs make full use of
their capital, technological and personnel resources.
</P>
<P>
"Promoting SOE reforms and development, in the final analysis,
means strengthening the role of the State-owned economy within the
socialist market economy," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
SOEs should adhere to the essential principle that our reform
does not mean privatization, and the Communist party leadership in
SOEs should play a core role in this regard, Jiang concluded.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
