<HEADLINE> Behind-Scene Story of Falun Gong Activities Exposed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A lengthy report by the People's
Daily and Xinhua News Agency has reviewed all the circumstances
surrounding the illegal gathering at Zhongnanhai, site of the
Chinese Government, by more than 10,000 Falun Gong practitioners
on April 25, and has unveiled Li Hongzhi's scheme behind this
incident.
</P>
<P>
The illegal gathering, targeting at the Chinese Communist Party
Central Committee and the State Council and disrupting the work of
the top leading organs of the Party and State, was the most
serious political incident since the 1989 political turmoil and
had an extremely bad impact both at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The report exposed the truth giving many details about the
illegality of the Research Society of Falun Dafa headed by Li
Hongzhi and the Falun Gong organizations under its control.
</P>
<P>
The gathering of some 6,000 Falun Gong practitioners on the
campus of Tianjin Education College of Tianjin Teachers University
was an omen of the illegal gathering on April 25.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi aimed to lead the Tianjin gathering to Beijing and
create a large-scale social disturbance.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi, who arrived in Beijing on April 22, spent 44 hours
in the city plotting with his followers the illegal gathering
outside the Zhongnanhai. He then flew to Hong Kong to remote
control the incident prior to the gathering in order not to be
suspected of organizing the gathering in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Li's purpose was soon spread among his followers, level by
level, via telephone calls.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing "headquarters" reported the situation of the April
25 gathering to Li Hongzhi in Hong Kong, and asked for his orders.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the Letters and Calls Departments of the General
Offices of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (
CPC) and the State Council required that Falun Gong practitioners
stop the illegal gathering. The Falun Gong "headquarters" then
conceded and dismissed the practitioners.
</P>
<P>
Ji Liewu, loyal to Li Hongzhi, was angry about the retreat, and
said that people who practice Falun Gong should be scared of
nothing, including death. "Bloodshed is sometime necessary. It
would have been good if bloodshed occurred," Ji said.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi, who has boasted that he understands the mysteries
of the universe, has made a wrong judgment of the situation and
overestimated his capability. Li is doomed to be sent to the court
of history. 
</P>
</TEXT>
