<HEADLINE> Li Hongzhi's Role in Illegal Gathering at Zhongnanhai (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Li Hongzhi, however, was not content, and considered his
actions up to then to be not influential enough. He even dismissed
a leader of the Beijing station, a branch of the Research Society
of Falun Dafa, for not obeying his orders.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi decided to make use of the event at Tianjin Teachers
University to cause a big storm. The Research Society of Falun
Dafa, manipulated by Li Hongzhi, then enlarged the entire scenario,
as Li expected.
</P>
<P>
On April 21, one day before Li Hongzhi sneaked into Beijing
from the United States, Wang Zhiwen, deputy head of the society,
incited the Tianjin station to lodge a protest at Tianjin Teachers
University.
</P>
<P>
On April 22, when Li Hongzhi arrived in Beijing, over 2,000
practitioners took part in the gathering. Wang Zhiwen expressed
his satisfaction when leaders of the Tianjin station reported the
situation, and he noted that the people could gather during the
day and disperse at night.
</P>
<P>
On April 23, the second day Li spent in Beijing, the number of
practitioners at Tianjin Teachers University proliferated to more
than 6,000 from the original 2,000. The Tianjin station prepared
to asked the practitioners to leave after it learned that this
gathering would be stopped by the authorities.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhiwen, however, said that the practitioners should not be
afraid and should take it as a test. Another 2,000 to 3,000 people
then gathered in front of the Tianjin Municipality People's
Government.
</P>
<P>
The situation in Tianjin was getting worse as Li arrived in
Beijing. But he not only aimed at Tianjin, but at Beijing as well.
What he deliberately planned was to cause social unrest on a
larger scale.
</P>
