<HEADLINE> Guangxi Falun Gong Kingpin Renounces Cult </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Huang Tenghui, chief of the Falun
Gong guidance station in this city in southwest China's Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region, has recognized the nature of the Falun
Gong cult and urged other followers to break their ties with it.
</P>
<P>
Huang, an employee of the Ronghu Hotel, began to practice Falun
Gong in 1996, and became chief of the Guilin station in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Huang could not accept the central authorities' ban of Falun
Gong cult when he learned the news at first. But he changed his
ideas recently, after local officials persuaded him out of the
fallacies preached by Falun Gong leader Li Hongzhi.
</P>
<P>
He told Xinhua that he was astonished to learn that Li Hongzhi
had consulted doctors and taken medicine when he was ill, as Li
claimed that Falun Gong practitioners can recover from any illness
without taking medicine and without the help of doctors.
</P>
<P>
He said facts show that Li's so-called "theory" is nothing but
superstition and is not in accordance with science.
</P>
<P>
Huang said that although Falun Gong had claimed that it had
nothing to do with politics, in fact, the illegal gatherings
around Zhongnanhai and local government buildings by Falun Gong
practitioners were antigovernment acts, showing that it is an
illegal organization.
</P>
<P>
Huang said he regretted having become a Falun Gong practitioner.
</P>
