<HEADLINE> Chinese Surgeon Wins World Honor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese surgeon Chen Zhongwei,
famed as the "father of severed limb replants," has been awarded
the Century Prize by the International Society of Micro-surgery.
</P>
<P>
An academician of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, Chen is
famed as the pioneer of China's micro-surgery.
</P>
<P>
He became world-renowned after he successfully replanted a
severed hand in 1963, for the first time in the world.
</P>
<P>
Two surgeons from Austria and the United States, respectively,
also received prizes from the Society, which awarded the prizes
for the first time this year. 
</P>
