<HEADLINE> China's Export Growth Rate Picking Up (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- China reported an export growth
rate of 7.5 percent in July, the second month of positive growth
this year, prompting experts to predict brighter export prospects
for the coming months.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the General Administration of Customs on
Thursday show that the export volume in July reached 17.34 billion
US dollars-worth.
</P>
<P>
China's general exports between January and July totaled 100.2
billion US dollars-worth, down 2.8 percent from the same period
last year. The overall trade volume reached 189.1 billion US
dollars-worth, up 5.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Imports in the seven months surged 16.6 percent to 88.9 billion
US dollars-worth, resulting in a trade surplus of 11.3 billion US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The declining rate of China's exports has been narrowing since
the beginning of the year, trade experts pointed out. The 2.8
percent decline between January and June was 1.8 percentage points
lower than that between January and June.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say that China's exports began picking up mainly
because exports of State-owned enterprises (SOE) have shown
positive growth and there has been a continuous growth of exports
by overseas-invested enterprises.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990812.0138 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Swimmer to Attempt English Channel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Chen Xiongguang may become the
first Chinese to swim the English Channel.
</P>
<P>
Chen, an ordinary company worker but a veteran swimmer, will
leave for Britain this weekend and try to swim the world-famous
strait from Dover in England to Calais in France around August 22,
according to a Beijing Youth Daily report today.
</P>
<P>
No Chinese has ever succeeded in swimming the English Channel,
even though a swimmer from Taiwan made an incomplete crossing in
the early 1990s, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The 38-year-old Chen started to consider a cross-Channel
attempt last year, when he won a race across the Qiongzhou Strait,
which separates the Leizhou Peninsula in south China's Guangdong
Province from the island province of Hainan.
</P>
<P>
"I think the Chinese people should be among the swimmers to
cross the English Channel," said the 1.68-m-tall champion of a
national winter swimming contest and the runner-up in an
international winter swimming championship in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Starting from Calais, the whole crossing will take about 12
hours, if Chen keeps up an average speed of 3,000 m per hour,
according to his plan.
</P>
<P>
Chen acknowledged that the biggest challenge he will have to
face is the low temperature of the sea water, which is between 13
and 17 degrees centigrade and has led to 80 percent of the
failures. The solutions may be special cold-proof swimwear and a
higher intake of calories.
</P>
<P>
The Dover Strait has long been a popular route for cross-
Channel swimmers because of its short distance. But strong and
frequent tidal movements and cold water make the feat rather
difficult.
</P>
<P>
A total of 4,200 people from 42 countries have made trans-
Channel attempts, but fewer than 400 have succeeded, the newspaper
said.
</P>
<P>
Chen, an employee of the Wenzhou Tobacco and Sugar Company in
east China's Zhejiang Province, has paid 1,350 pounds to a British
swimming association to acquire permission for the swim and pay
for a backup boat and navigation service.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990812.0139 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Export Growth Rate Picking Up (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Exports of SOEs have declined continuously since last January,
and the overall export volume in the seven months by SOEs added up
to 44.9 billion US dollars-worth, down 10.5 percent. But it was 2.
5 percentage points higher than that between January and June.
</P>
<P>
In July, SOEs reported a total export volume of 8.88 billion US
dollars-worth, up four percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, exports from overseas-invested companies in the
seven months reached 46.59 billion US dollars-worth, up 6.2
percent. The proportion of exports from those companies in China's
overall exports grew from 42.8 percent between January and July
last year to 46.5 percent in the same period this year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, China's exports of machinery and electronic
products have shown a strong growth rate of 11.3 percent, with an
export volume of 40.04 billion US dollars-worth.
</P>
<P>
Exports of other major export commodities, including textile
products, garments, footwear and toys, have also risen.
</P>
<P>
China's exports grew only 0.5 percent last year, as a result of
the financial crisis in the capitalist countries of Asia. The
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation and several
other relevant departments have taken a series of encouragement
measures to stimulate exports since the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the surge in imports was mainly due to a continuous
crackdown on smuggling since last year, increasing domestic demand
and a decline in the prices of commodities on international
markets.
</P>
<P>
The chief import products in the period were machinery,
electronic products and industrial-use raw materials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
