<HEADLINE> 2 Killed, 5 Injured in Armed Robbery in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed and five
others injured Wednesday in an unprecedented armed robbery in
Qom, a religious city about 100 kilometers south of the capital
Tehran.
</P>
<P>
An eyewitness said a group of armed robbers entered the city's
Mellat shopping mall at 22:45 local time (18:15 GMT) Wednesday and
then threatened shopkeepers to surrender their belongings and
money to them, the official Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA)
reported.
</P>
<P>
The robbery happened when the mall was almost closed and gold
sellers were busy collecting their jewels. The robbers, wearing
masks, grasped gold and 90 million rials (about 10,000
U.S. dollars) in cash from the shops, said the eyewitness.
</P>
<P>
The robbers began to open fire at shopkeepers and passers-by
indiscriminately as they tried to run away from the scene. The law
enforcement forces patrolling the area rushed to the scene upon
hearing the shots.
</P>
<P>
After running out of bullets, the robbers attacked customers
with knives.
</P>
<P>
Two people injured in the incident died Thursday, and two
others, including one of the robbers, were reportedly in critical
conditions, IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
A law enforcement official said there might have been five
robbers because five assault rifles were seized. The robbers have
not been identified yet, he added. 
</P>
