the militants who infiltrated the villages last Saturday, Air
Force Commander-in-Chief Anatoly Kornukov told reporters Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He confirmed the use of special and highly destructive weapons
to stop the militants, saying, "These highly effective weapons can
reach the gunmen in their foxholes, canyons and other places of
concealment." However, he denied any plan to bring in heavy
bombers or cruise missiles.
</P>
<P>
Kornukov said the number of rebels, estimated at 1,000-1,500 at
the beginning of the operation, has dropped significantly.
</P>
<P>
