<HEADLINE> Newcomers Fit In World Champions Suit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The world champions France will
test newcomers in a friendly against Northern Ireland when World
Cup star Zinedine Zidane and teenager sensation Nicolas Anelka
unfit for the match in Belfast next week.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Johan Micoud of French champions Girondins Bordeaux
and Paris St-Germain winger Laurent Robert were on Thursday
included in an 18-man squad for the August 18 friendly.
</P>
<P>
Anelka has just resumed training with his new club Real Madrid
for a week and Zidane has just came back from a knee cartilage
surgery.
</P>
<P>
Suspended Christophe Dugarry and Youri Djorkaeff will also miss
the match.
</P>
<P>
Squad:
</P>
<P>
Goalkeepers: Fabien Barthez (Monaco), Ulrich Rame Girondins
Bordeaux).
</P>
<P>
Defenders: Laurent Blanc (Inter Milan), Marcel Desailly, Franck
Leboeuf (both Chelsea), Lilian Thuram (Parma), Bixente Lizarazu (
Bayern Munich), Vincent Candela (AS Roma).
</P>
<P>
Midfielders: Alain Boghossian (Parma), Didier Deschamps(Chelsea)
, Johan Micoud (Girondins Bordeaux), Emmanuel Petit,Patrick Vieira
(both Arsenal).
</P>
<P>
Forwards: Robert Pires (Olympique Marseille), Sylvain Wiltord,
Lilian Laslandes (both Girondins Bordeaux), Laurent Robert (Paris
St-Germain), Tony Vairelles (Olympique Lyon). 
</P>
