<HEADLINE> Doohan to Miss Czech GP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 12 (Xinhua) -- World champion Mick Doohan
said Thursday that he would miss the Czech Grand Prix on August 22
due to injury in San Francisco, the United States.
</P>
<P>
Doohan, five times 500cc motorcycling world champion, got
injured on May 7 in a crash in his Honda during qualifying for the
Spanish Grand Prix at Jerez. He broke his right leg, shoulder and
left wrist.
</P>
<P>
"This is the race I had been aiming for to start racing again,
but we are going to have to wait a little longer," the Australian
said. "At the moment my arm isn't strong enough for racing,
although generally my recovery has been good."
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old has missed the last eight Grands Prix since the
Spanish Grand Prix. 
</P>
</TEXT>
