<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rise Sharply in Tokyo on Wall Street Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices rose sharply in Tokyo
Thursday, boosted by a rally on Wall Street Wednesday and the U.S.
dollar's upturn against the yen.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange surged 211.81 points, or 1.23
percent, from Wednesday's close to end at 17,422.97.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, advanced 17.80 points or 1.25 percent to 1,
438.4.
</P>
<P>
Trading remained sluggish, with turnover on the major section
totaling 322.86 million shares, compared with Wednesday's 325.40
million shares, as many market players were away for the summer
holidays this week.
</P>
<P>
Sumitomo Heavy Industries LTD. was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
After opening lower, the benchmark index stayed in plus
territory throughout the day, supported by the favorable movements
in the New York stock market and in the foreign exchange market,
traders said.
</P>
<P>
Share prices were higher in most business sectors, and export-
oriented issues attracted active buying, they said.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers outpaced
losers 720 to 431, with 135 shares remaining unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
