<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eight Die in Flood in Eastern Part of Qinghai Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Eight people have been confirmed
dead and 10 injured in a flood that hit the eastern part of
northwest China's Qinghai Province from August 4 to August 7,
according to the latest official figures.
</P>
<P>
The flood, caused by torrential rains, damaged a large number
of houses and highways, railways, and crop areas, causing economic
losses valued at 170 million yuan, said Sun Lin, an official with
the Qinghai Civil Affairs Department.
</P>
<P>
He said the flood swept across 15 counties and over 100
townships, affecting more than 200,000 people.
</P>
<P>
The flood also affected nearly 66,700 hectares of farmland,
with 23,300 hectares of crops totally destroyed.
</P>
<P>
It caused over 6,000 houses to collapse.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has organized emergency relief aid to
the disaster areas to help flood victims get over the difficulties
and return to normal life as soon as possible, Sun added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
