<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed higher Thursday on a strong technical
rebound.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index added
40.46 points or 5.87 percent to 728.96, the all-share Emas index
rose 12.99 points to 188.13, the Industrial Index added 88.34
points to 1,275.44 and the Second Board Index rose 9.95 points to
157.58.
</P>
<P>
Gainers led losers by 778 to 12 while 17 counters were
unchanged. and 110 counters untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's total turnover increased to 609.780 million shares
valued at 1.322 billion ringgit (about 347.894 million U.S.
dollars) from Wednesday's 333.666 million shares valued at 840.341
million ringgit (about 221.142 million dollars). 
</P>
