<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rebound on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices rebounded
Modestly on Singapore Stock Market Thursday, lifted by a rebound
in Wall Street after a tame Federal Reserves economic report.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) picked up 25.28 points
to end at 2,012.81 points in light dealings, regaining the
2,000-point level but off the intraday high of 2,026.51 points.
</P>
<P>
The total volume contracted to 219.35 million shares valued at
445.13 Singapore dollars (about 265.92 million U.S. dollars).
Gainers led losers by 150 to 146 with 149 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
AFP continued to top the volume list of the day as 15.68
million units of the stock changed hands. Hotung was the second
heavily traded share with a turnover of 10.88 million units.
SingTel was the next with 10.53 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
UOB F topped the actives chart as it climbed by 60 cents to
close at 11.10 Singapore dollars. DBS gained 40 cents to finish at
17.70 Singapore dollars. NatElect edged up 40 cents to end at 7.80
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SPH headed the descent of the day as it
plunged by 90 cents to close at 28.50 Singapore dollars. SPH 100
lost 80 cents to finish also at 28.50 Singapore dollars. SIA F
retreated 20 cents to end at 15.20 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said shares rose on the back of positive domestic news
and improving sentiment over U.S. interest rates.
</P>
<P>
They also noted that investors remained cautious despite the
upturn initiated by the Dow, pointing to underlying conditions
that
suggested a general upturn in interest rates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
