<HEADLINE> Impressive Growth In China's Housing Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- China continued increases in
real estate development and investment this year, with the revival
of the real estate market, according to the Ministry of
Construction.
</P>
<P>
The housing reform and increased housing sales replacing
government allocations have helped the country's housing markets,
according to an official at the ministry's real estate department.
</P>
<P>
To stimulate individual housing sales, commercial banks have
introduced mortgages to stimulate housing purchases.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show individual housing sales accounting for
70 percent of total housing sales so far this year and a decrease
in the amount of houses sold to government institutions and
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The country expects to add nearly 400 million sq.m. of housing
by the end of this year, or 50 million sq.m. more than for 1998.
Sharp increases are also expected in housing sales.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say that China's real estate business is growing in a
sound way and construction is expected to grow 15 percent annually
for the first decade of the next century. By 2005, China will have
added 1.5 billion sq.m. of housing in urban areas, 3.5 billion sq.
m. in rural areas, and rebuild 2.9 billion sq.m. of old houses.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
