<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 2.5 Million Mozambican Children Receive Polio </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, August 12 (Xinhua) -- About 3.64 million under-five
children have received polio vaccination throughout Mozambique in
the first phase of polio vaccination campaign, more than the
planned 3.3 million.
</P>
<P>
The campaign carried out from July 26 to 30 cover also children
of its neighboring countries along the border areas, Aurelio
Zihao, Mozambique's health minister said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The encouraging result is a result of the joint efforts by the
government, non-governmental organizations, and religious
organizations, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, about 3.3 million children, from six month to
five years of age, have been fed with vitamin A, nearly 97 percent
of the scheduled number, the Noticias daily reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The government has demanded grassroots units to mobilize
efforts of all sectors in the society to uproot polio in the
country, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique has promised to the World Health Organization to
eradicate polio by 2000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
