<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Games Host Embarrassed by Roof Tiles Falling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANDAR SERI BEGAWAN, Brunei, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Roof tiles
falling at the media center made the host of the Southeast Asian
Games so embarrassed that it took down all 150,000 tiles as a
precaution on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
An initial cascade of tiles last week, before the games began,
injured at least one policeman and crushed a police van, reports
said.
</P>
<P>
No one was hurt when more tiles fell Wednesday, but journalists
arriving at the center Thursday had difficulties getting around
roped-off areas as some 300 workers proceeded with the tile
removal.
</P>
<P>
"This is only a precaution. There is no danger of tiles falling,
" Ismail Damit, minister of development of oil-rich Brunei, told a
news conference.
</P>
<P>
He said the building structure is safe, and it would remain
watertight because of a metal roof under the ornamental tiles.
</P>
<P>
Some problems are normal on a construction site, he said.
</P>
<P>
The media center has been set up in a section, completed in May,
of the International Convention Center. Work was continuing on the
part where tiles fell, which overlooked an outdoor area set aside
as a smoking section for the media center.
</P>
<P>
Ismail said the builders had tested the fasteners to withstand
weights 2 1/2 times those of the tiles, and "we have to establish
why they did not work on the roof."
</P>
<P>
He said the first fall of tiles occurred a day after "
exceptionally strong" winds.
</P>
<P>
Now, he said, "we have decided not to take a chance on tiles
slipping down" at the part of the center serving as headquarters
for hundreds of journalists covering the games among some 2,400
athletes from 10 nations.
</P>
<P>
Brunei is host to the SEA Games for the first time. It plans to
play host to next year's summit of the Asia-Pacific Economic
Cooperation forum and use many of the venues constructed for the
games.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
