<HEADLINE> 25th National Sports Festival Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's 25th National
Sports Festival opened on Thursday at the Bogambara Stadium in the
central hill city of Kandy with over 2,000 sportsmen and women
participating.
</P>
<P>
The Olympic torch was lit by Sugath Tillekeratne, Asian Games,
Asian Championship and South Asian Games 400 meters gold medallist,
and Nirmala Kumari, South Asian Games 400 meters silver medallist.
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony was attended by General Anuruddha Ratwatte,
Minister of Irrigation and Power and Deputy Minister of Defense.
</P>
<P>
The 3-day festival has great significance as most of the
athletes selected for the forthcoming South Asian Federation Games
(SAFG) to be held in Nepal in September, are expected to
participate in the Games.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan President Chandrika Kumaratunga will be the cheif
guest at the closing ceremony on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, the main events include the men's and women's
4X440 meters relay, soccer, kabadi, volleyball and netball finals.
</P>
<P>
Last year the Western Province won the overall championship
with 64 gold medals. It is expected the province will dominate
this year's festival again. 
