<HEADLINE> Ham Producer to Expand Through Use of Foreign Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Chundu Foodstuffs Group, a
well-known ham producer based in the city of Luoyang in central
China's Henan Province, will use capital from Switzerland to
expand production.
</P>
<P>
Ertel A. Habiba, a Swiss investment company, will pump 30
million U.S. dollars into the central China conglomerate, local
sources said.
</P>
<P>
