Swiss company and the Chinese ham processor, 24 million U.S.
dollars will be used to expand the company's high-grade meat
products, and 6 million U.S. dollars will be used to finance
sideline production.
</P>
<P>
The Chundu Foodstuffs Group won fame for producing hams and
sausages, and has now grown into a conglomerate with diverse
businesses. Its main sideline business is manufacturing
pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
The group ranks high in China in both sales and pre-tax profits.
