<HEADLINE> Scenic City Steps up Urban Planning Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The popular scenic Chinese city
of Guilin has successfully completed a consultation event during
which it asked domestic and overseas experts to submit designs for
the around-the-city water supply system.
</P>
<P>
Institutions from the United States, Japan, and France, as well
those from Taiwan and Jiangsu Province's Southeast China
University have offered advice.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the city has done quite a lot to improve its
infrastructure and become more of an international city.
</P>
<P>
Last November, Guilin Prefecture and Guilin City, both of which
were under the jurisdiction of the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
regional government, were given approval to combine themselves
into one administrative unit.
</P>
<P>
This means a greater number of projects to be built in the new
city of Guilin, or greater Guilin, which now has an area of 27,800
sq.km. and a population of 4.8 million.
</P>
<P>
Because of Guilin's reputation as a tourist spot, it needs
stricter management and controls on construction work to avoid any
possible damage to its natural beauty and harmony, says one local
official.
</P>
<P>
He says they plan to build the new water system with a more
scientific design using drafts from overseas organizations.
</P>
