<HEADLINE> Northwest Chinese Province Benefitting From World Food Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Some 560,000 people in 10 poverty-
stricken counties in China's Qinghai Province are living better
lives thanks to assistance from the United Nations' World Food
Program (WFP), according to a local government official.
</P>
<P>
Chen Chengzhi, of the provincial foreign investment office,
says that Qinghai has built five reservoirs, more than 700
kilometers of waterways, 600 kilometers of roads, and 3,300
hectares of forested land with WFP help.
</P>
<P>
WFP started the projects in 1985 and two have been completed
and two others are underway. They have helped improve
agricultural conditions and the environment and increased grain
output, thereby providing food security and increased incomes.
</P>
<P>
They also helped provide tapwater, irrigation systems, primary
schools, and clinics in the impoverished areas and more than 130,
000 farmers and herdspeople have received training from WFP-
sponsored programs, 50,000 of them women, Chen says.
</P>
<P>
The province also benefited a great deal from loans provided by
the International Fund for Agricultural Development, he adds.
</P>
