<HEADLINE> Ancient Tombstones Discovered in Northeastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese archeologists have
discovered a number of tombstones dating back to the Liao Dynasty
(916-1125 A.D.) in Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
They are scattering in Qianshan Mountain near the city of
Anshan, archeologists report. They guess that the occupant of the
tomb must have been a person of high status and wealth, based on
an analysis of the images on the tombstones.
</P>
<P>
They say that the discovery is important for the study of the
development of Anshan during the Liao, which was founded by Qidan,
an ethnic group living in northern China who often clashed with
the central government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
