<HEADLINE> Shanghai Auctioning Off Debt-laden Hotel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 12 (Xinhua)-- The city of Shanghai plans to
auction off a 3-star hotel to help pay off its heavy debts, on
September 16.
</P>
<P>
The Tianma Hotel, which occupies 1.4 ha of prime ground,
accumulated losses because of poor management methods amidst a
period of general decline in the number of tourists in Shanghai.
It was built in 1987 and is one of the most famous hotels in
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Auction House is responsible for the sale and says it
is confident that the hotel will bring a good price because the
National Tourism Administration has decided not to approve new
tourist hotels for a 3-year period.  
</P>
