<DOCNO> XIE19990812.0245 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Preparing For 50th Anniversary Of People's Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Beijing is busy preparing for
the 50th founding anniversary of the People's Republic of China on
October 1.
</P>
<P>
Sources at the municipal preparatory committee say that
thousands of people have already taken part in a practice parade
on Tiananmen Square and 100,000 primary and middle school students
have been putting in background items.
</P>
<P>
There will be 90 floats in the parade representing 34 provinces,
autonomous regions, and municipalities, as well as Hong Kong,
Macao and Taiwan, and a military review to show China's newest
weapons for which military personnel are busy drilling.
</P>
<P>
Another 100,000 dancers and singers will be in the square at
night, many of them from China's various ethnic regions, and 8
factories are producing fireworks for the event. The fireworks
have patriotic names like "Chanting the Eulogy of the Motherland",
"Stars of Macao" and "Songs of the Century".
</P>
<P>
There will also be an exhibition on the 50 years of development
in Beijing and various celebrations in major parks.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the renovation work on Tiananmen Square that was
completed recently, the city has torn down 4 million square meters
of unlicensed structures to make thoroughfares and streets more
beautiful. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
