<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Tractor Exports up for the Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Exports of tractors grew about
12.6 percent in the first six months of the year, the best figures
for a two-year period, China Trade News reports.
</P>
<P>
Exports of tractors manufactured by 50 leading Chinese tractor
plants amounted to 344.40 million yuan (41.7 million U.S. dollars)
from January to June. The increase is mainly attributed to
increased sales of walking tractors to Southeast Asia, but exports
of caterpillar tractors, high-powered tractors, and other types
were also up.
</P>
<P>
China's traditional tractors markets are in Southeast Asia,
Africa, Central Asia, and Latin America.
</P>
<P>
China's overall exports for the first six months were worth 83
billion dollars, down 4.6 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
