<HEADLINE> Chinese World Horticulture Exposition Recognized As Scenic Spot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Yunnan Province in southern
China recently announced that the '99 World Horticulture
Exposition that is being held in the provincial capital, Kunming,
is one of the province's 11 best scenic spots.
</P>
<P>
The exposition opened on May 1 and will last through October
31. It has had more than 5 million visitors so far. It covers a
200-ha. area with displays of flowers and plants from around the
world and from all over China.
</P>
<P>
To attract more tourists, Yunnan has developed measures to
improve food, housing, transportation, and other services for the
event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
