<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, August 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The Federal Reserve said Wednesday that the U.S.
economy is still growing strongly with widespread labor shortages
reported nearly everywhere in the country.
</P>
<P>
In its latest survey of economic conditions around the country,
Fed found only scattered signs of mounting wage pressures and
little evidence of rising inflation in general. (US-Fed Survey)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW YORK -- Wall Street stocks rose higher Wednesday as the
networking company Cisco Systems reported strong earnings and the
Federal Reserve found little evidence of rising inflation
pressures in a report.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 132.65 at 10,787.80,
trimming almost all losses of 138 points in the three previous
sessions.
</P>
<P>
The broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index rose 20.50 at 1,301.93 and the technology heavy
NASDAQ index rose 74.87 at 2,564.98. (US-Wall Street-Closing)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- The Inter-American Development Bank (IDB)
approved a loan of 100 million U.S. dollars to Argentina on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be used to fund medical care projects, in
particular on health care services for the poorest and most
vulnerable sectors of the population.
</P>
<P>
The loan was granted on a 20-year term, with five years' grace
and a variable annual interest rate, which is 6.98 percent at
present. (Argentina-IDB-Loan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CARACAS -- OPEC members will discuss the possibility of
expanding the group at the summit to be held here at the beginning
of next year, a Venezuelan official said here Wednesday. (OPEC-
Summit-Expansion)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- The U.S. dollar rose to a five-month high
against the Brazilian real on Wednesday, as a result of unstable
foreign markets and Brazil's domestic politics.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. currency, on the rise for the last two weeks, rose on
Wednesday by 0.54 percent from Tuesday's close, and reached at mid-
session in the free market a rate of 1.875 reals (buying) and 1.
878 reals (selling).
</P>
<P>
This price was the highest it had come to since March 12 when
it stood at 1.91 reals (buying), and 1.92 reals (selling). (Brazil-
Currency)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BERLIN -- Signs of economic recovery have appeared, by and
large, in the Asian countries which were hit by
financial crisis in the past few years, the German Institute for
Economic Research said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
South Korea is likely to regain a fairly strong economic growth
this year while Thailand will see a very weak growth and Malaysia
may expect a rebound, said the report.
</P>
<P>
It predicted that the Indonesian economy will downslide again,
only at a slower speed than in 1998. (Asia-Financial Crisis-
Recovery) 
</P>
</TEXT>
