<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Encourage Development of Non-State Owned High-Tech Ventures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government has
adopted new policies to encourage development of non-state owned
enterprises, sources from the Ministry of Science and Technology
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Today's China Daily reported that the regulation, drawn up by
the ministry and State Economic and Trade Commission, is designed
to create a healthy climate for the research and development of
high-tech projects and the commercialization of scientific
discoveries.
</P>
<P>
The government supports non-State technical firms in applying
to participate in national scientific research programs.
</P>
<P>
The development of high-tech research and the prompt transfer
of the latest scientific discoveries to mass production will be
the focus of a national conference on technical upgrading slated
for August 23-26.
</P>
<P>
The daily said the regulation is among one of over a dozen new
policies announced recently or to be issued in the following weeks
to boost technical invention and high-tech research, in efforts to
promote China's sustainable economic development.
</P>
<P>
The government has already announced a policy for encouraging
scientists and technicians to establish high-tech ventures with
their discoveries as part of the shares of the ventures.
</P>
<P>
The government has also offered 1 million yuan (120,000 U.S.
dollars) as loan guarantees for medium and small-sized technolgy-
based enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
