<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bosnia-Herzegovina Plagued With High Jobless Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The number of registered
unemployed people in Bosnia-Herzegovina has exceeded that of the
employed for the first time, an official employment body announced
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The jobless people in this country have numbered 406,177, with
261,177 people from the Muslim-Croat Federation and 145,000 from
the Republic of Srpska, the Employment Bureau of Bosnia-
Herzegovina was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
More than half of the unemployed are graduate students waiting
for jobs, who totaled 253,782 in number. Ex-servicemen are the
second largest jobless group, with a total number of 147,820.
</P>
<P>
Other sources said around 406,000 people in this country have
jobs.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment rate in Bosnia-Herzegovina, which stood at
nearly 40 percent at the end of July, is the highest in Europe.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
