<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Agassi, Kafelnikov Roll into ATP Third Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 11 (Xinhua) -- American Andre Agassi and
Russia's Yevgeny Kafelnikov showed why they have held the No. 1
ranking this year as they coasted into the third round Wednedsday
at the ATP Championship in Cincinnati, the United States.
</P>
<P>
Coming off one of his worst matches of the year, Agassi bounced
back by pulling away for a 6-4, 6-1 victory over Frenchman Arnaud
Di Pasquale.
</P>
<P>
Seeded fourth, Kafelnikov rebounded from Sunday's loss in the
du Maurier Open final as he dumped Sweden's Jonas Bjorkman 6-1, 6-
4 in just over an hour.
</P>
<P>
Second seed Patrick Rafter of Australia, who held the No. 1
ranking for one week at the end of July, will begin defense of his
title tonight against Daniel Vacek of the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
Three other Americans joined Agassi into the round of 16.Two-
time champion Michael Chang of the United States got past eighth
seed Alex Corretja of Spain 6-3, 6-7 (5-7), 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Justin Gimelstob surprised ninth seed and fellow American Todd
Martin 6-4, 6-4; and Chris Woodruff eliminated No. 13 Thomas
Enqvist of Sweden 6-1, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Also, No. 11 Tommy Haas of Germany struggled past Frenchman
Fabrice Santoro 6-0, 7-6 (1-7), 6-3; and No. 15 Nicolas Lapentti
of Ecuador downed American Jan-Michael Gambill 6-0, 7-6 (7-3).
</P>
<P>
In unseeded play, American Jim Courier was forced to retire
during his match with Cedric Pioline of France. Pioline was
leading 6-7 (5-7), 7-6 (7-4), 2-0, when Courier was unable to
continue with leg cramps.
</P>
<P>
Today's win improved Agassi's record to 21-3 in his last 24
matches and 17-1 in his last 18 matches against Frenchmen. Agassi
was coming off a 6-1, 6-4 loss to Kafelnikov in the semifinals at
Montreal.
</P>
<P>
Last year's runner-up, Sampras extended his winning streak to
18 matches on Tuesday as the top seed outlasted Jan Siemerink of
the Netherlands 7-6 (11-9), 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Fifth seed Tim Henman of Britain, sixth seed Gustavo Kuerten of
Brazil and seventh seed Richard Krajicek of the Netherland all
cruised into the third round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
