<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar's Yangon Airways Extends Domestic Flight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Yangon Airways, a joint
venture between state-run Myanma Airways (MA) and private-run
Myanmar Mayflower (MMF) Co Ltd, has extended its flights to two
border towns in the country's eastern Shan state, according to
Thursday's official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
The extended flights to Tachilek and Kengtung from Yangon,
which began Wednesday, will operate via Heho on every Monday and
Wednesday, it said.
</P>
<P>
Since its establishment in October 1996, the Yangon Airways has
been operating regular and chartered flights directly between
Yangon and Bagan, Mandalay, Heho, Tachilek, Kengtung, Dawei, Myeik
and Kawthoung.
</P>
<P>
There are altogether three Myanmar airlines flying domestically
-- state-owned MA, joint-venture Air Mandalay and Yangon Airways.
</P>
<P>
The Yangon Airways was initially formed jointly by the MA and
the Krong Sombat Co Ltd of Thailand and started flying in October
1996.
</P>
<P>
Later, the share of the Thai company in the joint-venture
airline was taken over by the MMF in August 1997.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Myanmar Airways International, a
Myanmar-Singapore joint venture, flies externally to seven
destinations and there are also 18 foreign airlines having regular
flights to Myanmar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
