<HEADLINE> International Peacekeepers Arrest Terrorists in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The international police force
and the international peacekeeping force arrested 78 terrorists in
Kosovo on Tuesday, peacekeeping force spokesman Jan Josten
announced in Pristina on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the massive arrests indicated that the
international peacekeeping forces have started to strengthen the
maintenance of public order in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The international peacekeepers arrested 60 armed Albanian
terrorists in the Kosovo Liberation Army (KLA) uniforms and seized
a large amount of weapons in a building located in Gnjilan.
</P>
<P>
In Prizren, they arrested five Albanian terrorists who were
kidnapping civilians, and in Ska Mitrovica, 10 Albanian terrorists
were also arrested.
</P>
<P>
Since the Yugoslav troops and police left Kosovo in early June,
the KLA has taken advantage of the tolerance and connivance of the
international peacekeepers and launched aggressive terrorist
assaults on non-Albanian residents, hence creating a "law vacuum"
in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
However, the KLA has recently run into more conflicts or even
bloodshed with the peacekeepers.
</P>
<P>
On August 8, the 478-strong international police force from 10
countries began joining force with the peacekeepers in maintaining
public order. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
