<HEADLINE> IDB Offers Argentina 100 Million U.S. Dollars in Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) approved a loan of 100 million U.S. dollars
to Argentina on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be used to fund medical care projects, in
particular on health care services for the poorest and most
vulnerable sectors of the population.
</P>
<P>
The loan was granted on a 20-year term, with five years' grace
and a variable annual interest rate, which is 6.98 percent at
present. 
