<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manchester United Wins First Match of Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Manchester United claimed their
first victory of the season with a 4-0 win over Sheffield
Wednesday 4-0 in English Premier League on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Aston Villa defeated Everton 3-0 at Villa Park to
snatch the league lead ahead of Arsenal on goal difference with
maximum points from two games.
</P>
<P>
Leeds United also took three points with their record signing
Michael Bridges scoring his first goals for the club with a hat-
trick in a 3-0 win at Southampton. His goals came in the 10th,
51st and 72nd minutes.
</P>
<P>
Leicester City beat Coventry City 1-0, leaving the Sky Blues
without a point or a goal from their two games.
</P>
<P>
In the Manchester United-Sheffield Wednesday match, Paul
Scholes opened United's tally at Old Trafford in the ninth minute,
lashing in left-footed off a Ryan Giggs cross. Cole then hit a
post before Dwight Yorke made it 2-0 in the 35th minute with a
fierce header off another Giggs cross.
</P>
<P>
United's three trophies from last season -- the European Cup, F.
A. Cup and Premiership -- were paraded before the 54,000 fans at
half time before Andy Cole made the score 3-0 with a deflection at
the post off a Teddy Sheringham shot.
</P>
<P>
Norwegian Ole-Gunnar Solskjaer, scorer of United's winning goal
in the European Cup final and the club's third top scorer in the
league last season after Yorke and Cole, completed the rout with
the fourth six minutes from time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
