<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0030 GMT, August 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA -- Ethiopian government troops have killed or
captured 1,103 of the 1,378 Oromo Liberation Front (OLF) and
Alithad militants in eastern Ethiopia bordering with Eritrea, the
Ministry of Defense said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The remaining rebel forces were forced to flee in disarray. It
was reported that prior to the latest operation, the government
troops have killed 653 and captured 283 Oromo rebels since this
May. (Ethiopia-Rebels)
</P>
<P>
---
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The U.N. Security Council Wednesday appointed
Switzerland's attorney-general, Carla Del Ponte, to the position
of the prosecutor of the U.N. war crimes tribunals for the former
Yugoslavia and Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
The 15-nation Council, in a unanimous resolution, endorsed the
nomination by U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan last week.
</P>
<P>
Del Ponte will take up her new post on September 15, when
Louise Arbour of Canada, who has been U.N. prosecutor since
October 1996, steps down to be a judge on Canada's Supreme Court.
(UN-Tribunals-Prosecutor)
</P>
<P>
---
</P>
<P>
OTTAWA -- The metalized mylar insulation blanket was
significantly linked to last September's Swissair crash, Canadian
investigators announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Transportation Safety Board of Canada, the
insulation blanket used inside the bulkheads of aircraft was a
significant factor in the spread of fire aboard doomed Swissair
Flight 111.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Canadian media reports said the U.S. Federal
Aviation Administration (FAA) is soon expected to order the
metalized mylar insulation blankets replaced on nearly 700
commercial airliners within four years. (Canada-Swissair
Investigation)
</P>
<P>
---
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- At least one person was killed and more than 100
others were injured as a tornado touched down in the downtown area
of Salt Lake City in Utah State of the United States Wednesday,
reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The reports quoted local authorities as saying that the black,
swirling cloud struck about 1 p.m. (GMT 1700), uprooting trees and
tents set up for a retailers convention. It also damaged the roofs
of the Delta Center, home of the Utah Jazz basketball team, and
the Salt Palace Convention Center. (US-Tornado)
</P>
<P>
---
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The United Nations High Commissioner for
Refugees (UNHCR) on Wednesday expressed concern over intimidation
of the Serb population in Kosovo, U.N. spokesman Fred Eckhard said.
</P>
<P>
Serbs in the ethnic Albanian-dominated province are in many
cases "first sent a warning letter to leave their homes then
threatened in person and finally assaulted", Eckhard quoted UNHCR
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Serb population in Pristina, capital of Kosovo, is down to
some 2,000 from a pre-war level of 20,000, UNHCR figures show. (UN-
Serbs) 
</P>
