<HEADLINE> China Takes Four Golds at Military World Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, August 11 (Xinhua) -- China had a bright day at the
Military World Games on Wednesday although the sun was partially
eclipsed.
</P>
<P>
Their Judokas won three gold medals and one silver to grab most
of the four golds the Chinese delegation collected, apparently not
affected by the astronomical event widely seen in Europe on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Pan Song scored China's first ever men's judo title at the
Military World Games when he beat Dutch Ben Sonnemans with a crisp
one-bon action in the over-100kg category.
</P>
<P>
Wang Jingling triumphed in the women's under-48kg category
while the women's under-52kg title went to compatriot Wang Jinyan.
</P>
<P>
Chinese judo team leader Wang Jinping said the team had
performed better than expection and reached the pre-Games target
of three golds.
</P>
<P>
China's triathlon athletes also struck gold by winning the
women's team title.
</P>
<P>
Xing Lin, Wang Dan and Li Bo combined for a total of six hours,
30 minutes and four seconds for the title. France was second
while United States third. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
