<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rain Brings Disasters, Compensation to Shanghainese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 12 (Xinhua)-- Heavy rain has brought serious
damage to ordinary people and businesses in this east China
metropolis, but the damage is being duly compensated for by the
Shanghai branch of the People's Insurance Company of China (PICC).
</P>
<P>
What had been lingering drizzle turned into downpours over the
past two months here, resulting in over 3,900 households and some
750 companies suffering losses.
</P>
<P>
The company paid out a record 70 million-plus yuan, which
helped those affected to restore normal life and production
quickly.
</P>
<P>
Fang Zhimin, deputy general manager of the Shanghai branch of
the PICC, said that many companies and individuals had not
received compensation because they had not taken out property
insurance coverage.
</P>
<P>
He said that, according to estimates by meteorological
departments, there will be a concentration of tornadoes, heavy
rain and tidal waves striking Shanghai in the second half of this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
