<HEADLINE> Severe Drought in Western Liaoning Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 12 (Xinhua) -- There has been a severe drought
in the western region of northeast China's Liaoning Province since
mid-June, leaving large areas of crops ruined and some rivers and
wells dry.
</P>
<P>
According to provincial government sources, 21 counties of the
five cities in western Liaoning are being seriously affected by
the drought caused by scant rainfall and persistent heat.
</P>
<P>
The drought has damaged 760,000 hectares of crops, among which
230,000 hectares were totally destroyed.
</P>
<P>
In the hardest-hit county of Jianchang, 14 small rivers and 260
wells dried up, leaving over 20,000 villagers and more than 30,000
livestock without water.
</P>
<P>
Provincial government leaders have inspected the drought-
stricken areas and relief efforts are underway to help those
affected overcome their difficulties and keep losses at a minimum.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
