<HEADLINE> Peru, Ecuador Sign Agreements for Closer Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Peru and Ecuador Wednesday signed
seven agreements to enhance bilateral cooperation in border
development, science and technology, free trade, customs and fight
against crime.
</P>
<P>
These documents were signed here by Peruvian Foreign Minister
Fernando de Trazegnies and his Ecuadorian counterpart, Benjamin
Ortiz, in the presence of Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori and
his Ecuadorian counterpart, Jamil Mahuad.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday morning, the two presidents met for the first time
since the two countries signed the Brazilia peace accord three
months ago.
</P>
<P>
Peru and Ecuador ended a 100-year-long border dispute with the
erection of the last boundary mark on their common borders on May
13. 
</P>
</TEXT>
