<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Numbers of Tourists Dwindle in Italy This Summer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 11 (Xinhua) -- As the Summer vacation season
reaches its peak, fewer tourists are passing vacation in Italy,
spurring losses in the tourism industry, according to a report
released Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A study carried out by an association of restaurant and bar
owners, Fipe, found that tourism dwindled by 1.5 percent between
June and August, as 2.2 million fewer vacationers are present in
Italy.
</P>
<P>
The report, which gathered information from 400 night clubs,
bars and restaurants across Italy, showed the most significant
drop to be in seaside tourism.
</P>
<P>
Fipe noted that the drop in these areas could be explained by
the Kosovo war, which caused many to rethink their holiday plans
and steer clear of the area which is Italy's closest point to the
troubled region.
</P>
<P>
Figures also showed that tourism had slipped in some regions
along the Adriatic coast and south island of Sicily.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
