<HEADLINE> U.N. Agency Concerned about Threats against Serbs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) on Wednesday expressed concern
over intimidation of the Serb population in Kosovo, U.N. spokesman
Fred Eckhard said.
</P>
<P>
The Serb population in Pristina, capital of Kosovo, is down to
some 2,000 from a pre-war level of 20,000, UNHCR figures show.
</P>
<P>
The 78-day U.S.-led NATO air strikes against Yugoslavia ended
in June, but a string of incidents had happened since then.
</P>
<P>
Serbs in the ethnic Albanian-dominated province are in many
cases "first sent a warning letter to leave their homes then
threatened in person and finally assaulted", Eckhard quoted UNHCR
as saying.  
</P>
