<HEADLINE> East Timor Attack under Investigation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Mission in East Timor (UNAMET) is investigating an attack which
killed two local students, U.N. sources confirmed Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The attack took place Wednesday at a gathering of students in
Vikeke where two participants were shot to death, U.N. spokesman
Fred Eckhard said.
</P>
<P>
"So far we have no other information on dead and wounded," he
said, noting that the incident is under investigation.
</P>
<P>
Eckhard said U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan's personal
representative for East Timor Jamsheed Marker arrived in Jakarta
Tuesday night for meetings with high-ranking officials of the
Indonesian Government on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday he is scheduled to meet President Habibi.
</P>
<P>
The incident took place prior to a ballot to determine special
autonomy or independence for East Timor, former Portuguese colony.
The territory was annexed by Indonesia in 1976. The vote for its
future was set for August 30.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
