<DOCNO> XIE19990812.0318 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liberian Plane Crash Kills Police Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Liberia's police chief Joe Tate
and several other senior police officers were killed Wednesday in
a plane crash near Monrovia, the country's capital.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here from Monrovia quoted a government
spokesman as saying that the eight-seater plane crashed near a
highway where it was trying to make an emergency landing after a
flight from Maryland County in southeastern Liberia.
</P>
<P>
The plane was heading for Roberts International Airport on the
outskirts of the west African state's capital. But it ran out of
fuel when it was trying to find a suitable place for emergency
landing and crashed, according to report.
</P>
<P>
Tate, a cousin of Liberian President Charles Taylor, was a
prominent figure on the country's political stage. He was a
member of Taylor's militia during Liberia's civil war before
joining his administration later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
