<HEADLINE> Alleged U.S. Gunman Surrenders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The white supremacist who
allegedly wounded five people in Los Angeles in California State
of the United States surrendered Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Buford O'Neal Furrow used a high-powered gun and
burst into a Jewish community center in Los Angeles and sprayed
the lobby with 20 to 30 shots, wounding five people, including
three boys attending day camp, and then walked away.
</P>
<P>
Furrow, who surrendered to investigators in Las Vegas in Nevada
State, would also be charged in the slaying of a postal worker who
was shot Tuesday near the community center.
</P>
<P>
He told investigators that he wanted this to be "a wake-up call
to America to kill Jews."
</P>
<P>
The violence in Los Angeles was the latest shooting at
workplaces and schools in the United States, and brought immediate
calls for stricter gun control and measures to protect children.

