<HEADLINE> Tornado Hits U.S. Salt Lake City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 11 (Xinhua) -- A tornado touched down in the
downtown area of Salt Lake City in Utah State of the United States
Wednesday, damaging buildings and causing dozens of injuries,
reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The reports quoted local authorities as saying that the black
funnel uprooted trees and tents set up for a retailers convention.
It also damaged the roofs of the Delta Center, home of the Utah
Jazz basketball team, and the Salt Palace Convention Center.
</P>
<P>
However, authorities had no immediate comment on the number of
injured or on whether there were fatalities.
</P>
<P>
The downtown area looked like a disaster zone with trucks
overturned, power lines down, windows blown out, shards of glass
everywhere, and police and firefighters attending to dozens of
injured, the reports said. 
</P>
